LEGAL NOTICE

Date: 10.01.2026

To,
The Chief General Manager,
National Highways Authority of India (NHAI),
PIU-Udaipur

Subject: Demand for Extension of Time, Payment of Running Bills, and Appointment of Arbitrator u/s 11
Ref: Contract Agreement for NH-758 (Km 0 to Km 45)

Sir,

Under instructions from M/s. Rajputana Infra Projects Pvt. Ltd., we state as follows:

1. Handover of the site was delayed by 78 days against the agreed 15 days from LOA, due to pending forest clearances and farmer agitation, severely impacting our client's mobilization.
2. NHAI has failed to release payment for the last three running bills.
3. Drawings for the grade separator were delayed by 4 months.
4. Despite our client's repeated applications, Extension of Time (EOT) has not been granted.

We hereby demand an Extension of Time of 14 months and payment of ₹38.50 Crore towards delayed site possession and unpaid bills. 

If this demand is not met within 15 days, we shall invoke arbitration and approach the Hon'ble High Court.

Yours faithfully,
Advocate for Contractor
